text.tspan: Prevalence of Alzheimer's disease and other dementias, World, 1990 to
Prevalence of Alzheimer disease and other dementias, measured as the prevalence per 100,000 people. This is shown as the
rate across all ages (not age-standardized), and the age-standardized rate which assumes a constant population structure over
time to adjust for impacts of population aging and changing age structure.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
